50|$|The ancient Greek {{concepts}} of honour (timē) included {{not only the}} exaltation of the one receiving honour, but also <b>the</b> <b>shaming</b> <b>of</b> <b>the</b> one overcome by the act of hubris. This concept of honour resembles a zero-sum game.|$|R
